               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460330-name-1030" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460330-name-1030" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460330-name-1030" type="surname" value="MYERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460330-name-1030" type="given" value="MENDLEWITZ"></interp>MENDLEWITZ MYERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in London-road, and am a general dealer. On the 4th of March I had a number of pairs of braces hanging outside my shop—about two o'clock I was told something—I looked, and missed a few pairs of braces—I could not say how many—they have not been found, but I know I lost them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460330-name-1031" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460330-name-1031" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460330-name-1031" type="surname" value="EASTEBBROOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460330-name-1031" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN EASTEBBROOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to the prosecutor—on the 4th of March I was standing outside the shop—I saw the prisoner run by and take several pairs of braces off the gas pipe—I could not go after him at the time because there was nobody outside but myself—in about five minutes he came back and looked into the shop—I told the young man, who ran and took him—I am sure he is the lad who took the braces.</p>
